# Tacet — local secrets template.
#
# Copy this file to `.dev.vars` (which is git-ignored) to run locally with real
# secrets, or skip it entirely: `npm run dev` works with safe local fallbacks and
# needs NONE of these. These matter only when you deploy to your own Cloudflare
# account. Never commit real values.

# Signs the session cookie. Generate a strong random value for any real deployment:
#   openssl rand -hex 32
# Local dev uses a built-in throwaway fallback if this is unset.
SESSION_SECRET="replace-with-a-long-random-string"

# Cloudflare Turnstile (bot protection on registration). Optional — the challenge
# is only enforced when both are set. Get them from the Cloudflare dashboard.
TURNSTILE_SECRET=""
TURNSTILE_SITE_KEY=""

# Optional: open social web discovery.
#   OPENWEB_INSTANCE — a Mastodon-compatible home for the REST discovery shim.
#   OPENWEB_SEED     — comma-separated @user@home handles for the generic AP seed.
# OPENWEB_INSTANCE="mastodon.social"
# OPENWEB_SEED="@Gargron@mastodon.social,@dansup@pixelfed.social"

# Optional: AUTHORIZED FETCH (read-only). Lets stricter homes (e.g. Mastodon secure
# mode) serve public content by HTTP-signing outbound GETs. All three are needed, and
# AP_ACTOR_ID must be a publicly reachable URL serving /api/openweb/actor. Generate a key:
#   openssl genpkey -algorithm RSA -pkeyopt rsa_keygen_bits:2048 -out ap_private.pem
#   openssl rsa -in ap_private.pem -pubout -out ap_public.pem
# Then paste the PEMs here (private stays secret; public is published in the actor doc).
# AP_ACTOR_ID="https://tacet.social/api/openweb/actor"
# AP_PUBLIC_KEY="-----BEGIN PUBLIC KEY-----\n...\n-----END PUBLIC KEY-----"
# AP_PRIVATE_KEY="-----BEGIN PRIVATE KEY-----\n...\n-----END PRIVATE KEY-----"
